.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script></p><p> The &#39;Übermensch&#39; world tour will be the <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/big-bang">Big Bang</a> rapper&#39;s third solo world tour and will also mark his first in over seven years, per <a href="https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2025-02-06/entertainment/kpop/GDragon-announces-world-tour-for-new-album-bermensch/2236565"><em>Korea JoongAng Daily</em></a> . His last was 2017&#39;s &#39;World Tour Act III: MOTTE&#39;, which recorded 654,000 attendees across 36 shows, breaking the record for the highest K-pop soloist tour turnout at the time.</p><p> G-Dragon&#39;s impending tour will be in support of his upcoming solo comeback with his third full-length album &#39;Übermensch&#39;, out February 25. The record was first announced earlier this week, making it his first body of work in seven years. It will also be his first studio album since he dropped 2013&#39;s &#39;Coup D&#39;Etat&#39;. </p><div class="td_block_wrap tdb_single_content tdi_86 td-pb-border-top td_block_template_2 td-post-content tagdiv-type" data-td-block-uid="tdi_86" data-io-article-url="https://www.nme.com/news/music/g-dragon-new-single-home-sweet-home-featuring-taeyang-daesung-3814913"><div class="tdb-block-inner td-fix-index"><p> G-Dragon debuted as the leader of YG Entertainment boyband <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/big-bang">Big Bang</a> in 2006. He later launched his solo career in 2009 with his studio album &#39;Heartbreaker&#39;, which was followed by the EP &#39;One of a Kind&#39; and album &#39;Coup d&#39;Etat&#39;. These subsequent releases spawned hits like &#39;Crayon&#39;, &#39;That XX&#39; and &#39;Crooked&#39;.</p></div></div><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/g-dragon-2025-ubermensch-world-tour-tickets-dates-more-3835360">G-Dragon announces kick-off shows in Goyang, South Korea, for 2025 &#39;Übermensch&#39; world tour</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
